Linear Search vs Binary Search

Linear Search:
Best Case: Element found at index 0.
            Time Complexity: O(1)

Average Case: Element found at any index between 0 to n-1.
            Time Complexity: O(n)

Worst Case: Element found at index n-1 or not found.
            Time Complexity: O(n)


Binary Search:
Best Case: Element found at mid where mid = (low + high)/2.
            Time Complexity: O(1)

Average Case: Element found after some splits.
            Time Complexity: O(log n)

Worst Case: Element found at extreme ends or not found.
            Time Complexity: O(log n)




Which Algorithm is More Suitable?
Binary Search is more suitable for an e-commerce platform because:

    -->  Binary Search is much faster for large number of products.
    -->  Time Complexity of Binary Search is O(log n). It reduces search time significantly.
    -->  Best in real-world applications where millions of products exist.